annotationA: NADH dehydrogenase (ubiquinone) 51 kDa subunit is a flavoprotein and iron-sulfur-containing oxidoreductase that catalyzes the oxidation of NADH to NAD. It is a component of the mitochondrial electron transport complex I, which is part of the oxidative phosphorylation pathway. It may have a role in regulating aggression behavior
annotationB: Pyruvate kinase; Potassium ion binding; magnesium ion binding; pyruvate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: glycolytic process; myoblast fusion; somatic muscle development; phosphorylation
